add

public void add(Object executable)

Give the Executor methods that its clients can invoke via RMI. A client that asks for some interface in its QoS will be able to invoke any of the methods of that interface on the Object that implements them.

When an Entity has more than one Object for command logic and more than one of them implements the same interface, the last one added takes precedence. For example, given 

  Executor e;
  e.add(A);
  e.add(B);

If both A and B implement some interface C, then B's implementation of C is the one that clients will use.

Projectors give precedence to interfaces implemented by ViewInterpreters that implement the tagging interface CommandLogic. See Projector.java.

Each interface will become part of the aggregate QoS offered by this Entity. 





Parameters:
executable - an object implementing some number of interfaces
